contentrichtext.text: {{Wiktionary}} '''Colonial Secretary''' may refer to: * [[Secretary of State for the Colonies]], the British Cabinet minister who headed the Colonial Office, commonly referred to as Colonial Secretary * [[Chief Secretary]], originally Colonial Secretary, the official in many British Colonies who headed the day-to-day functions of the colony's government, deputy to the Governor * [[Colonial Secretary (New Zealand)]], the chief administrator of New Zealand from 1840 to 1907 ==See also== * [[Provincial Secretary]] {{disambig}}
